# Gitleaks ignore list — fingerprints for confirmed false positives in history.
#
# Format:  <commit-sha>:<file>:<rule-id>:<line>
#
# The .gitleaks.toml allowlist would normally cover these going forward, but
# rules can change between gitleaks versions and re-flag history. This file
# locks the known-false-positives at the commit level so a CI gitleaks job
# stays green even if the allowlist regexes need to be re-tuned.
#
# Each line documents WHY the finding is a false positive.

# ── SHA-256 content hashes in pan-file-manifest.json (discord.md entry)
# Hash value `adb903c6...` is sha256(commands/pan/discord.md), not a Discord
# token. Discord tokens are dot-separated base64, not 64-char hex.
74ab15dd7a4907d884971174d973b7f1b3c20034:.claude/pan-file-manifest.json:discord-api-token:106
161993305ee93baa2b1f2f6425405937373a2f13:.claude/pan-file-manifest.json:discord-api-token:106

